pageContext.claim: “And the crazy New York Times, which was a dead newspaper -- when I ran, it was dead as a doornail. A month before I ran, Doug, I held up a New York Times. It was like what you get thrown in your face at a supermarket. It was like a thing. It just like flew away. There was nothing. And now it's doing very well.”
pageContext.analysis: The New York Times has been consistently profitable for the past ten years, so Trump is simply making up this claim.
